Package: jxlr
Type: Package
Title: JPEG XL Image Format Support for R
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Klaus Brunner <klaus.brunner@gmail.com>
Maintainer: Klaus Brunner <klaus.brunner@gmail.com>
Authors@R: c(person("Klaus", "Brunner", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "klaus.brunner@gmail.com"))
Description: Provides functions to read, write, and manipulate JPEG XL (JXL) 
    image files in R. JPEG XL is a modern image format that offers superior 
    compression efficiency and quality compared to traditional formats while 
    maintaining compatibility with existing workflows. Supports both lossy and 
    lossless compression modes, RGB and RGBA images, and follows the same 
    conventions as the 'png' and 'jpeg' packages.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/klausbrunner/jxlr
BugReports: https://github.com/klausbrunner/jxlr/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
Depends: 
    R (>= 4.0.0)
Imports:
    Rcpp (>= 1.0.0)
LinkingTo: 
    Rcpp
Suggests: 
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    png,
    jpeg
SystemRequirements: C++17, libjxl (>= 0.7.0), pkg-config
